<br>
Let me address a few points. <br>
<br>
I have viewed guides/GMs, if not the same exact way you do Arleanna, at least in a similar way. They do have the power to suspend or ban, so I avoid them. They have never done anything to improve my enjoyment of the game -- in the cases where they have attempted to help, they have either made it worse, or at best, they have done something for me that I could have done, in less than half the time. This is the reason why I have avoided guides and GMs. <br>
<br>
I would never view cops as CS reps. And I would not view guides/GMs as cops. In effect, they are CS reps, but they behave like corrupt cops with little fear of retribution. They will help those who kiss their asses, and refuse help to those who don't. Example: players died in lguk on king raid, one corpse get stuck in wall, guide summoned it. Just for the hell of it, the players asked if the guide could summon the other corpses -- even though they were not stuck. The guide naturally refused, saying it would be illegal. Players said something to the effect of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    &quot;heheh ok, we had to try&quot;.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The guide then started chatting with the players, about her upcoming wedding to another guide. The players all promised to attend her wedding. She was so happy about this, that she said <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>     &quot;I shouldn't be doing this, but here goes...&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and promptly summoned everyone's bodies. <br>
<br>
Incidentally, if I really wanted to fuck with the guides, I could have posted the chat, and screenshots -- the guide she was getting married to was the prick who gave me a warning over the player name &quot;Natural&quot;. Wouldn't it have been fucking spiffy to show up at the wedding and announce that I'd posted it, getting her thrown out of the guide programme as a wedding gift. So yeah, you may think I'm a bad guy, but I could sure as hell done a lot worse, than tell a guide to go fuck himself. <br>
<br>
So the point is -- this last encounter that I posted, where I fucked with the guides, yes of course I went overboard, and of course it was unwise of me to say those things. It was a spur of the moment thing. As Bowynn quite correctly pointed out, it was a long overdue FUCK YOU, for all the shit the guides and GMs have done all this time. <br>
<br>
Do guides have to put up with a lot of bullshit? Oh hell yes. But until the above incident, they never had to put up with bullshit from me. If you get bullshit at work, you may have to accept it, because you need the money. But if you get bullshit doing something you volunteered for, you have NO reason to complain about bullshit. None. Zip. I remember back when my father volunteered to help out and drive some handicapped people around, they complained because the guy who normally drove them had a much better car. They didn't wanna drive in his car; they all fought to ride in the fancier cars, and my old man stood there waiting for the &quot;losers&quot; to dejectely come ride in his not-so-fancy car. Now, my dad loved helping people, but he promptly said &quot;fuck this&quot; after that. <br>
<br>
Ie., if guiding isn't fun, then quit. <br>
<br>
And here's the diabolical kicker: if enough people gave enough guides shit, Verant might just have to invest some more money into their CS programme and hire more GMs, pay them better etc. I dunno how likely that is, but if that's what it'll take to keep customers paying, then it will happen. And if enough people cancelled their accounts, well -- same deal. <br>
<br>
Another issue about the guides/GMs on this server: I have played extensively on Vallon, as a Shank. The Shanks are a hardcore roleplaying, no-mercy PvP player killer guild. They are revered, and viewed as a very honorable bunch by the decent players on the server. But they are hated (and harrassed) by the d00ds. And that means we would get petitioned a lot. False accusations were made constantly, our accusers would lie and accuse us of training, corpse camping -- all the things that they would do to us. If a guide/GM were to make a mistake, and punish me because of those lies, I would forgive them, because it is very hard to see through the lies. You'd have to be pretty smart to figure out exactly what happened. But they hardly ever did. Sure, some mistakes were made, but my god, those guys were on the ball like you wouldn't believe it. <br>
<br>
And appart from that job, you should fucking SEE the Vallon Zek GM events! The last GM event I took part in, on The Tribunal, was the bixie invasion. This event consisted of giant GM controlled bixes who shouted &quot;BZZzzzZZZzz!&quot; and slaughtered people, newbies and high lvl people alike. It was an absolute, utter joke, and a classical &quot;Lets blow some steam off by fucking with our customers&quot; GM event. <br>
<br>
Just after this happened on The Tribunal, I took part in a GM event in the same area, on Vallon Zek. It was an absolute ball. A GM controlled dark elf female wizard rallied her crowd of players against a dwarven male palladin -- oh my god what a fight, it went from Nektolus, through the commonlands, into Freeport, and I think back to the commonlands again. It was a full blown roleplay event, and we had a shitload of fun. The GMs were really good, and in character at all times. After the event was over, they walked around rezzing people. Fat fucking chance the crew on The Tribunal would bother doing that. <br>
<br>
Guides and GMs aren't cops. But if they were, then the lot we have been blessed with here on The Tribunal, are a bunch of stoned, lobotomized Keystone Cops, and Vallon Zek's are Sherlock fucking Holmes. <br>
<br>
This fact, that I have seen with my own eyes, how good the crew on Vallon are, compared to these miserable jizmops, is the key element in my frustration. <br>
<br>
What will I do next? No idea. I'm mighty tempted to go with DAoC, and become a Shank once again, but would need an upgrade, which I don't see myself doing right now. <br>
