Most importantly, guides can (if they choose) be a person to vent to when a policy or player makes the game less enjoyable. That doesn't mean you have to be a punching bag, but there were many times that there was nothing I could do but listen to the player and sympathize with them. Sometimes that was enough. Some players just needed to know that their frustration was heard and understood.<br>
