<br>
BULLSHIT<br>
<br>
Verrant created the system in which they chose CS - whether or not Guides are paid affiliates of the VICS System, THEY ARE A PART OF THE SYSTEM.  If I convince my neighbor to KILL you does it matter if I pay him or not?  Verrant created the institutions of their Customer Service - They created the position of Guides.  So is VI responsible for the actions of their Guides?  YES.<br>
<br>
And as for the analogy of dealing with a Cop, I can tell a cop to fuck himself and as long as I don't resist arrest or break any other laws he can do fuckall about it.  There might be some bullshit charge he can hit on me, but being disrespectful to a police officer is NOT a crime.  Cussing at a Police officer is NOT a crime.  So that whole analogy is a bit off base if you ask me.<br>
<br>
I just get tired of everyone going &quot;Don't blame the Guides, they work all this time and get $10 a month for it.&quot;  They fucking volunteered.  I have no sympathy for someone who hits themself in the nuts repeatedly with a ball peen hammer and then complains because their balls hurt.  If you are being a guide for the $10 a month, retire now.  If you think they're underpaid for what they do, don't apply to be a guide.  It's not like there's a lottery every month to pick the CS People.  I don't sympathize with Guides for the amount of work they do for the pay - I can say I might respect or understand that they're doing it because it might be fun, and I'm generally respectful to Guides... only once have I ever had to contradict one... but that was a GM.  To make a long story short, I was unencumbered and fell 15 loc points in WW for 10k.  I reported and petitioned and the GM said he jumped off of that cliff and it 10k'd him.  I said to read the report and mentioned that I didn't have inside info on the coding - but I thought it was nearly impossible to fall from an elevation of 15 locs for 10k, let alone with safefall maxed.  What happened?  He read, reconsidered, and got a rez.<br>
<br>
So I'm sorry but the VI CS people aren't Martyrs - they may not get paid for what they have to do, but they volunteered for it none the less.<br>
<br>
So the excuse of VICS Guides aren't paid and VICS Guides aren't part of VICS is bullshit to me.  They created the institutions of their CS, and people volunteered to be guides.  So don't pull the fucking martyr card on it.<br>
<br>
-Holdan <p><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/mccannk/tag2.bmp></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uthemorganfriendtoall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Themorgan Friend to All</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 2:26:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: </span><hr size=1> I was a guide for a while, I liked being a guide. I never had anyone be rude to me. The reason I quit is because the other guides on the server would log on and the que would be full.  They would say &quot;I'm not here to guide I want to explore velious for a while&quot;, this was when velious was available to guides and not players yet. so I would be there with 20 petitions trying to get through them and there would be 3 other guides exploring velious and ignoring the job that they were supposed to be doing in the first place. I admit that I explored Velious a few times,  but I would only do it if there were no petitions, which happens more than you'd think. Ever since then I've had a low opinion of guides I think they are lazy and self serving, for some one that is there for costumer service. <br>
